<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
  <% include partials/header %>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:wght@300;400;600&family=Karla:wght@300;400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <style>
    :root {
      --gold: #c9963a;
      --gold-light: #e8bc68;
      --deep: #1a0f00;
      --cream: #fdf6ec;
      --muted: #8a7560;
      --text: #3a2810;
    }

    .styled-page {
      background: var(--cream);
      color: var(--text);
      font-family: 'Karla', sans-serif;
      padding-bottom: 40px;
    }

    .page-header {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 40px 24px 36px;
      position: relative;
    }

    .page-header::after {
      content: '';
      display: block;
      width: 60px;
      height: 2px;
      background: var(--gold);
      margin: 24px auto 0;
    }

    .page-header h1 {
      font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
      font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 4vw, 2.2rem);
      font-weight: 300;
      letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      color: var(--deep);
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .page-header .subtitle {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.25em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--gold);
      margin-top: 8px;
      font-weight: 500;
    }

    .section-nav {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 20px 24px 10px;
    }

    .section-nav a {
      color: var(--gold);
      text-decoration: none;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      transition: color 0.3s;
      padding: 4px 0;
    }

    .section-nav a:hover { color: var(--deep); }

    .section-nav .sep {
      color: var(--gold-light);
      margin: 0 10px;
    }

    .page-intro {
      font-size: 1.12rem;
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--muted);
      text-align: center;
      max-width: 700px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 20px 24px 10px;
      line-height: 1.85;
    }

    .page-content {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 20px 24px;
    }

    .page-section {
      padding: 32px 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(201, 150, 58, 0.15);
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(20px);
      transition: opacity 0.5s ease, transform 0.5s ease;
      scroll-margin-top: 80px;
    }

    .page-section.visible {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }

    .page-section:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

    .page-section h2 {
      font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
      font-size: 2rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--gold);
      margin-bottom: 16px;
      line-height: 1.2;
      transition: color 0.3s;
    }

    .page-section:hover h2 { color: var(--deep); }

    .page-section p {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      line-height: 1.85;
      color: var(--text);
      margin-bottom: 14px;
    }

    .page-section ul {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
    }

    .page-section ul li {
      padding: 8px 0;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      line-height: 1.85;
      color: var(--text);
    }

    .page-section ul li::before {
      content: '\2022';
      color: var(--gold);
      font-weight: bold;
      display: inline-block;
      width: 1em;
    }

    .page-section a {
      color: var(--gold);
      text-decoration: none;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gold-light);
      transition: color 0.3s, border-color 0.3s;
    }

    .page-section a:hover {
      color: var(--deep);
      border-color: var(--deep);
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <% include partials/menu %>
    <div class="container bg-light">
      <div class="styled-page">
        <div class="page-header">
          <p class="subtitle">Youth Programs</p>
          <h1>Shree Swaminarayan Yuvak Mandal</h1>
        </div>

        <div class="section-nav">
          <a href="#mission">Mission</a><span class="sep">&middot;</span>
          <a href="#objectives">Objectives</a><span class="sep">&middot;</span>
          <a href="#contributions">Contributions</a>
        </div>

        <p class="page-intro">At the turn of the new millennium, the late Mahant Sadguru Purani Swami Hariswarupdasji
          of Bhuj Mandir envisioned a group that would unite the youth of our religion, residing globally. His goal was
          to empower the youth to take on the challenge of moving our satsang forward among their fellow haribhakto in
          this materialistic world. After years of dedicated effort, this vision was realised.</p>

        <div class="page-content">

          <div class="page-section">
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>Given the youthful congregation in Sydney, Australia, it was decided that this would be the ideal launch
              location of the international branch. In 2003, in the presence of esteemed Swamis from Bhuj, including the
              current Mahant Sadguru Purani Swami Dharmanandandasji, Shree Swaminarayan Yuvak Mandal Sydney was
              established, marking the beginning of Swami&rsquo;s vision.</p>
            <p>From our humble beginnings of involving the youth in decorating hired halls for festival celebrations to
              organising the first Shibir in Australia, SSYM Sydney has thrived over the years. Today, we are proud to
              offer a wide range of activities that are designed to foster personal growth, community service, and
              spiritual development among our youth.</p>
          </div>

          <div id="mission" class="page-section">
            <h2>SSYM Sydney Mission Statement</h2>
            <p>SARVA-JEEV-HITAAVAH | For the betterment of all living beings</p>
          </div>

          <div id="objectives" class="page-section">
            <h2>SSYM Sydney Objectives</h2>
            <ul>
              <li>Promote Hindu Sanatan Dharma, as directly authenticated by Bhagwan Shree Swaminarayan and
                authenticated by Bhuj Mandir Santo.</li>
              <li>Grow and develop our youth to ensure the sustainability of the Sampraday for future generations.</li>
              <li>Empower and inspire our youth to not only sustain but enrich their active engagement in satsang,
                fostering a lifelong spiritual journey.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div id="contributions" class="page-section">
            <h2>Contributions to Australasian Community</h2>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Weekly YM Sabha:</strong> Every Friday, we hold an interactive YM Sabha for yuvaks from 7 PM
                to 8:45 PM, providing a space for spiritual discussions, learning, and friendship. At the same time, a
                dedicated separate YM Sabha is held for yuvatis, fostering a supportive environment to empower our young
                female haribhakto.</li>
              <li><strong>Youth Support:</strong> Our dedicated youth support programs provide guidance and mentorship,
                helping young individuals navigate the challenges of modern life while staying rooted in their spiritual
                values.</li>
              <li><strong>Increasing Bhakti:</strong> Through Bhakti Boosters such as bhajan mornings, Prabhat feris,
                and other satsang sessions, we aim to deepen the spiritual connection of our youth, encouraging them to
                embrace and practice Bhakti in their daily lives.</li>
              <li><strong>Decoration:</strong> We actively involve our youth in creating grand decorations for all temple
                festivals. This enhances the festive atmosphere and allows our youth to showcase their artistic
                expression while creating engaging experiences for visiting haribhakto.</li>
              <li><strong>Themed Events:</strong> Events such as Amazing Race, Maharaj&rsquo;s Kitchen Rules, and trivia nights
                provide fun and engaging ways for youth to bond, challenge themselves, and apply their skills in
                creative contexts.</li>
              <li><strong>Social Events:</strong> Social gatherings such as barbeques and outings provide a platform for
                youth to bond, share experiences, and build lasting friendships.</li>
              <li><strong>Shibirs:</strong> We organise Shibirs (spiritual retreats) that offer immersive experiences in
                satsang, personal development workshops, and opportunities for self-reflection and growth.</li>
              <li><strong>Charity Events:</strong> We regularly organise charity initiatives such as blood drives, tree
                planting, food drives, and step-a-thons. These events benefit the community while instilling
                responsibility and compassion in our youth.</li>
              <li><strong>NarNarayan Dev Cup:</strong> This annual sports event brings together young haribhakto from
                SSMB Sydney and ISSO Sydney, promoting physical fitness, teamwork, and a healthy competitive spirit.</li>
              <li><strong>Sports:</strong> Regular sports activities such as badminton and darts help our youth stay
                active, healthy, and engaged in positive pursuits.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Through these efforts, we aim to nurture the next generation of leaders who will carry forward the
              legacy of our beloved Bhagwan Shree Swaminarayan.</p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  <script>
    var observer = new IntersectionObserver(function (entries) {
      entries.forEach(function (e) {
        if (e.isIntersecting) { e.target.classList.add('visible'); observer.unobserve(e.target); }
      });
    }, { threshold: 0.15 });
    document.querySelectorAll('.page-section').forEach(function (el) { observer.observe(el); });
  </script>

  <% include partials/footer %>
</body>

</html>
